{
  "text": "2.4. Quaternion-K\u00e4hler moment map. For any S 1 -symmetry (i.e., isometry) on a quaternionK\u00e4hler manifold M one can define its moment map ( [CITATION_1] ) in the following way. Let \u03c9 i (\u00b7, \u00b7) := g(I i \u00b7, \u00b7), where I 1 , I 2 , I 3 is a local quaternionic base. Then the 4-form \u2126 :",
